info.title: SendIT API
info.description: ## Introduction The SendIT API offers seamless carrier integration in your IT infrastructure. In this API you will find actions for following features: * Print label / Generate print job or pdf * Transmit data to the carrier (closing). * Reprint label * Cancel label ## Connecting to the API To connect to our REST API please use following URL: http(s)://hostname:4210/api/v2/ There is also a SOAP API for legacy customers - please use following URL to connect to the SOAP API: http(s)://hostname:42000/SendITWebService/V2/ You can also find the url in the installation protocol file that you have received after installation on premise. For request examples, please download following Postman collection. You can download Postman [here](https://www.getpostman.com/downloads/) to read and execute the sample requests. ## Authentication For authentication please use the parameters "webServiceUser" and "webServicePassword". You can find the credentials in the installation protocol file. If you do not know your credentials and can not find your installation protocol file, please get in touch with your project manager or [support-sendit@prologis.de](support-sendit@prologis.de) for further advice. ## General Information All label layouts are generated based on the specifications of the carrier. If you need any customer specific changes, please get in touch with your sales contact. ## Further Documentation For a list of shipping types please here. Please have a look at the examples and models below to find a detailed description on each request.

post.summary: Close the shipments for the designated shipper, client and shipping location.
post.description:
Triggers the data transmission to the carrier as well as the manifest generation. The manifest can also be printed on a windows printer.
You can use this request multiple times per day.

post.summary: Print label for a package / Generate print job/pdf of a label.
post.description:
Use this request to print a label.
This request needs to be executed for each label of a shipment. You can assign packages to shipments by using the parameter "shipmentID". Samples for shipments with more than one package are contained in the Postman collection (see description above).
In the response you will receive the tracking number, tracking url, package barcode and depending on the selected printmode the print job/pdf.

ShippingLocationID.description:
The shipping location id defines the warehouse location from where the package is shipped. Please have a look at the configured shipping locations in SendIT WebClient.
Example: Our example company "Doe Corporation" ships from two different warehouses: Munich (ShippingLocationID=MUC) and Frankfurt (ShippingLocationID=FRA). The primary key for all carrier configurations in SendIT is the combination of ShippingLocationID and ClientID. Also the consignor's address is configured using the combination of those two values. By sending the ShippingLocationID "MUC" the consignor's address in Munich will be used. By sending the ShippingLocationID "FRA" the consignor's address in Frankfurt will be used.
| ShippingLocationID | ShipFromCity |-------------------------|----------------- | MUC | Munich | FRA | Frankfurt

ClientID.description:
The client id indicates the company that ships the package. Please have a look at the configured clients in SendIT WebClient.
Example: Our example company "Doe Corporation" holds two subsidiary companies: "Doe Red" (ClientID=DoeRed) and "Doe Blue" (ClientID=DoeBlue). They ship from two different warehouses - Munich (ShippingLocationID=MUC) and Frankfurt (ShippingLocationID=FRA). The primary key for all carrier configurations in SendIT is the combination of ShippingLocationID and ClientID. Also the consignor's address is configured per combination of those two values. By sending the ClientID "DoeRed" the carrier contract 1 and the consignor's address "Doe Red" will be used. By sending the ClientID "DoeBlue" the carrier contract 2 and the consignor's address "Doe Blue" will be used.
| ClientID | CarrierContractNo | ShipFromAddress1 |-------------|---------------------|--------------------- | DoeRed | 0000000001 | Doe Red | DoeBlue | 0000000002 | Doe Blue

SubCompanyID.description:
With subcompanies you can handle multple consignor's addresses for the same client id / shipping location id.
Example: The subsidiary company "Doe Red" of our sample company has two major brands: "Doe Moon" (SubCompanyID=DoeMoon) and "Doe Star" (SubCompanyID=DoeStar). By sending the SubCompanyID "DoeMoon" the consignor's address "Doe Moon" will be used. By sending the SubCompanyID "DoeStar" the consignor's address "Doe Star" will be used. Both will use the same carrier contract details that are connected to the client / shipping location.
| ClientID | ShippingLocationID | SubCompanyID | ShipFromAddress1 |-------------|---------------------|--------------|--------------------- | DoeRed | MUC | DoeMoon | Doe Red - Doe Moon | DoeRed | MUC | DoeStar | Doe Red - Doe Star

StationID.description:
The station id indicates which printer is used for label printing. Please have a look at the configured stations in SendIT WebClient.
In case of pdf generation please use the StationID "PDF". In case of print job generation (PrnResponse) please use the StationID "PRN".

PrintMode.description:
There are different print modes:
| PrintMode | Description |--------------|------------------ | Device | Print will be executed on a thermal printer (no driver installation required) or on a laser / inkjet printer (Windows driver required).
Following thermal printers are supported: Zebra, TSC and cab printers, as well as all printers with ZPL-emulation.
Project specific other printers can be implemented (Avery, Sato, TEC, Intermec). Please get in touch with your sales representative if you need other printers. | PRN | The print job will be stored on a network share. | PrnResponse | The print job will be retured in printer syntax in the response. | JPG,PNG,GIF | The label will be stored on a network share.
For graphic generation the chargeable add-on module "SendIT.GrafikPrint" is required. | PDF | The label will be returned as pdf file base64 encoded in the response.
In addition, it will be stored on a network share.
For pdf generation the chargeable add-on module "SendIT.GrafikPrint" is required.

ShippingDate.description:
The shipping date of the package. You can usually pass the current date in this field. The shipping date indicates, when SendIT transmits the data to the carrier. If you send a package with a shipping date in the future, this package will not be transmitted to the carrier with a closing request unless the shipping date is reached.
Please provide the date in the culture format of the application server. The default is English format with MM-dd-yyyy.

shipmentID.description: The shipment id can be used to group the packages and transmit them grouped as shipments to the carrier. The shipment id needs to be the same for all packages that are in a shipment. Sample: You have two shipments. One shipment consists of two parcels, the other shipment consists of one parcels. Here is an overview on how to provide the shipmentID: Request data of the first parcel of the first shipment: shipmentID = 0001 package -> id = 0001-1 package -> position = 1 package -> count = 2 Request data of the second parcel of the first shipment: shipmentID = 0001 package -> id = 0001-2 package -> position = 2 package -> count = 2 Request data of the first parcel of the second shipment: shipmentID = 0002 package -> id = 0002-1 package -> position = 1 package -> count = 1 Please refer to the Postman collection for examples on multi parcel shipments (download link above).

In some logistics processes your might need to only close specific packages.
The shipper combine id can be used to mark packages for a closing request. You can provide the shipper combine id also in the load or closing request to only close packages with the designated shipper combine id.

TrackingID.description:
The tracking id can be used to assign a tracking id in your system.
In this case SendIT will no longer generate a tracking id based on the configured number ranges.
SendIT will use the provided tracking id for building the tracking link.
In addition the provided tracking id will be insert in the carrier barcode on the label.
            
In most cases this is only used for cargo shippers, when you want to reuse your internally generated GS1-SCC numbers (NVE).
Please inform your project manager if you want to use this field.

type.description:
Identifier for the transmission of additional services. Following services are available:
| Type | Description |--------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | AdditionalLabel (AdditionalLabel1-AdditionalLabel2) | Request an additional label (e.g. additional label for LiIon batteries). | AdditionalHandling | Service for packages that require additional handling. (not processable packages for sorting machines). | AdditionalPacking (AdditionalPacking1-AdditionalPacking2) | Add additional packings to a shipping unit (e.g. sandwich pallets, etc.). | AdditionalReference (AdditionalReference1-AdditionalReference5) | Add additional reference to the packages. These references will be transfered to the carrier if supported. | AdvanceInstructions | Advance instruction service. Only for usage with DHL (Vorausverfuegungen - Unzustellbarkeitsnachricht, Sofort zurueck, Keine Nachbarschaftszustellung). | Advice (Advice1-Advice2) | Service for free text advice. This service is used for general cargo freight carriers only. | Amazon | Service for Amazon data (PO numbers and ASN number). | B2B | Service for B2B-delivery. | B2C | Service for B2C-delivery. | Battery (Battery1-Battery5) | Service for special handling of batteries (metal / ion). | BillingAddress | Service for divergent billing address. The carrier will send the invoice for the shipment to this address. | DeliveryAddress | In combination with pickup service, a package will be sent directly from the pickup address to the delivery address. | Bulk | Bulk service. Indicator for oversize / overweight shipments that require additional handling. | BypassInboundDepot | Service to bypass the inbound depot | CheckContentUponDelivery | Driver Service for checking the content of the parcel at delivery time | Climate | Climate service. Triggers the GOGREEN for DHL etc. | COD | Cash-on-delivery service. | CollectiveCustomsClearance | Service for the collective clearance of customs like UPS World Ease | ConsolidatedDelivery | All packages of a multicolli shipment must be delivered at one time | Confidential | Confidental service. | Cooling | Service for regrigerated shipment of goods. | CMR | Request a CMR to be generated in addition to the shipping label. | CustomsBroker | Customs broker service. Currently only supported by FedEx. | CustomsState | Indicator for T1-customs shipments. Please only use this indicator in coordination with your project manager. | DailyPrice | Daily price service. Only valid for general cargo freight carriers. Please only use this service in coordination with your project manager. | DeliveryInstructions | Delivery at work service. Used for department delivery. | DeliveryWithoutPOD | Delivery without POD/signature. | DriverAdvice | Pre-advice service. The driver will send shipping notifications per e-mail. Some carriers also support notifications using sms or phone. | EKAER | Service for the hungarian electronic trade and transport control system | Exchange | Exchange service. Service for exchanging broken deliveries. Your package will be exchanged with a return packages. | Express | Express service (time-definite services and fixed date services). | Floor | Service for floor delivery. | Fragile | Service for fragile goods that require extra careful handling. | Hazard | Hazard service (also for limited quantities), general data. | Hazard (Hazard1-Hazard5) | Hazard service (also for limited quantities), material data. | HomeDelivery | Delivery inside the receivers home. Mostly used for carriers that support furniture transport services. | Identification | Receiver identification service. The carrier will check the receivers passport, age, etc. | ImportRegistration | Service for import registration. | Incoterm | Delivery incoterm (for a list of all incoterm types e.g. DAP, EXW, etc., please click [here](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incoterms)). | Info (Info1-Info9) | Additional information service. This service is used for general cargo freight carriers to book additional services. Please get in touch with your project manager if you are planning to use this service. | Insurance | Additional insurance of the shipped goods. | Installation | Service for installing the goods at delivery | InternalBarcode | You can provide a value for an internal barcode on the label in this service. Please only use this service in coordination with your project manager. | ItalianPublicInvestmentCodes | You can provide CIG (Codice Identificativo Gara) and CUP (Codice Unico di Progetto) for italian shipments in this service. This is required for public procurements that exceed a value of EUR 1.500,00. Please only use this service for italian carriers. | LiftingRamp | Lifting ramp service. Indicator for shipments that need to be delivered using a lifting ramp. | ManualProcessing | Manual processing service. Indicator for shipments that require manual processing. | NeutralDelivery | Service for a neutral delivery. | Notification | Notification service. The carrier will send shipping notifications per e-mail. Some carriers also support notifications using sms or phone. | PackagingRemoval | Driver must remove packaging at delivery time. | Parcelshop | Parcelshop service. The carrier will deliver to a parcel shop (DHL Packstation, UPS Access Point, etc.). | Pickup | Pickup service. The carrier will collect the shipment at the consignee's address and deliver it to the ship from address. There will be no printed label - the carrier will bring a label at the collection. | PrivateAddress | Private address service. Some carriers offer special services for b2c shipments. | ProcurementLogistics | Service for ProcurementLogistics. | ReplyAdvice | Service for shipment with reply advice | Return | Print an additional return label. | SafePlace | Service for specifying safe place for driver to leave shipment, e.g. garage. | SelfCollection | Service for self collection | ShortStorageTime | Service for a short storage time | Signature | Explicitly request the consignee's signature at delivery. | Small | Service for a Small Package Shipment. | Trackable | Request a trackable service. Indicator for SendIT Freight Cost Calculator for product determination. | Tyre | Special service for shipping tyres. | UnpackAppliance | Service for unpacking appliance. | IncotermThirdPartySenderAddress | In combination with incoterm service, ThirdParty sender address. | IncotermThirdPartyReceiverAddress | In combination with incoterm service, ThirdParty reciver address.
Some services can be transmitted more than once. In this case please number the services accordingliy. If you have one advice, please use service type Advice1. If you have two advices, please use the service types Advice1 + Advice2.
Please keep in mind that not all of the listed additional services are available for all carriers. If there are any questions about the availablity of additional services for your carriers, please get in touch with your carrier's sales department.
